
[1]affable

   AF'FABLE, a. [L. affabilis, of ad and fabulor. See Fable.]

   1. Easy of conversation; admitting others to free conversation without
   reserve; courteous; complaisant; of easy manners; condescending;
   usually applied to superiors; as an affable prince.

   2. Applied to external appearance, affable denotes that combination of
   features, which invites to conversation, and renders a person
   accessible, opposed to a forbidding aspect; mild; benign; as, an
   affable countenance.
